ZH: 我们不应该徒劳地浪费时间。
EN: We should not waste time in vain.

ZH: 他的努力是徒劳的，因为他没有做好准备。
EN: His efforts were in vain because he was not well prepared.

ZH: 不要为了个人私利而徒劳地争吵。
EN: Don't argue in vain for personal gain.

ZH: 我们已经尽力了，但是最终还是徒劳了。
EN: We tried our best, but it was all in vain in the end.

ZH: 这些批评是徒劳的，因为他并不在意他人的看法。
EN: These criticisms are futile because he doesn't care about others' opinions.

ZH: 她试图劝说他改变主意，但是却是徒劳的。
EN: She tried to persuade him to change his mind, but it was all for naught.

ZH: 你的抗议是徒劳的，他们根本不在乎。
EN: Your protests are futile; they simply don't care.

ZH: 即使你不断努力，有时候仍然会徒劳无功。
EN: Sometimes, even if you try your best, it may still be in vain.

ZH: 他花了很多时间研究，但最终结果却是徒劳的。
EN: He spent a lot of time studying, but the final result was in vain.

ZH: 他从不放弃，即使努力看似徒劳。
EN: He never gives up, even when his efforts seem futile.

ZH: 这个项目打了很多擦边球，结果变得徒劳无功。
EN: This project played a lot of tricks, but the result was fruitless.

ZH: 我们不能因为失败而感到徒劳，要继续努力。
EN: We should not feel futile because of failure; we should keep trying.

ZH: 不要为了一点小矛盾而大费周章，那样只是徒劳。
EN: Don't make a big fuss over a small disagreement; it's just a waste of effort.

ZH: 我们不应该被一些细节问题困扰，那样只是徒劳。
EN: We shouldn't be bothered by trivial issues; it's just futile.

ZH: 我们的许多努力都是徒劳的，因为我们没有明确的目标。
EN: Many of our efforts were in vain because we didn't have a clear goal.

ZH: 对于那些不愿改变的人，劝说是徒劳的。
EN: Persuasion is futile for those who are unwilling to change.

ZH: 他的倾诉是徒劳的，因为没有人会听他说。
EN: His venting is futile because there is no one to listen to him.

ZH: 不要在那些只会嘲笑你的人面前徒劳争辩。
EN: Don't argue in vain in front of those who will only mock you.

ZH: 我们要学会避免徒劳地抱怨。
EN: We should learn to avoid complaining in vain.

ZH: 尽管困难重重，我们仍然不应该徒劳地放弃。
EN: Despite the difficulties, we should not give up futilely.
